  "name": "Morrison CPB Hemolysis Credibility Assessment — MRL 2 Minimal Profile",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. This UnitOfAssurance evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. The intended use scope — identifying peak shear-stress hemolysis exposure at rated pump speeds of 3000–5000 RPM for adult CPB patients — is described in the bound Requirement and Claim records. Full 13-factor assessment is documented in hasCredibilityFactor: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Submitted under ProfileMinimal; structured COU linkage deferred pending registry onboarding.",
